
	<sn><md>## Biochemical Tests in Microbiology{.text-center}

&gt; Biochemical tests are laboratory methods used to **identify microorganisms** based on their `biochemical activities`.

 Since microorganisms *differ* in their ability to ++metabolize nutrients++, ++produce enzymes++, or ++utilize certain compounds++, these tests help in `distinguishing between closely related species`. They are essential tools in clinical diagnosis, food safety testing, and microbiological research.

