<sn><md>### Purpose of Biochemical Tests{.text-center}

1. `Identification of Bacteria` – Different bacteria show unique metabolic reactions.
2. `Clinical Diagnosis` – Helps in determining the causative agent of infections.
3. `Industrial Applications` – Used in food and pharmaceutical industries for quality control.
4. `Research` – Provides insights into microbial physiology and enzyme activity.
</md></sn><sn><md>## 5 Biochemical Tests {.text-center}

| **Test Name**              | **Principle**                                                                 | **Procedure**                                                      | **Result**                                                                                                                                                                             |
| -------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Catalase Test**          | Detects *catalase enzyme* that ++breaks down hydrogen peroxide++ into water and O₂. | Add a few drops of hydrogen peroxide to a bacterial colony.        | Immediate `bubbling` = positive.                                                                                                                                                         |
| **Urease Test**            | Detects urease enzyme that ++hydrolyzes urea to ammonia and CO₂++.                | Inoculate bacteria in urea broth and incubate.                     | `Pink` coloration = positive.                                                                                                                                                            |
| **Oxidase Test**           | Detects ++cytochrome c oxidase enzyme++ in the electron transport chain.          | Apply tetramethyl-p-phenylenediamine reagent to bacterial culture. | `Purple/blue` color within 30 seconds = positive.                                                                                                                                        |
| **Indole Test**            | Detects ability to break down ++tryptophan into indole++.                         | Grow bacteria in tryptophan medium, add Kovac’s reagent.           | `Red ring` at surface = positive.                                                                                                                                                        |
| **Triple Sugar Iron Test** | Differentiates bacteria based on ++sugar fermentation and H₂S production++.       | Inoculate bacteria into TSI slant.                                 | - Yellow butt &amp; slant = lactose/sucrose fermentation <br> - Yellow butt, red slant = glucose only <br> - Black precipitate = H₂S production <br> - Gas bubbles/cracks = gas production |
